The paper deals with cross-modal information retrieval, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval of information from large collections of data, including text and multimedia. The paper also proposes an approach to model texts using a featured graph, which involves graph theory and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for image representations, which is a common technique in computer vision, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a dual-path neural network for learning multi-modal representations of information, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
